---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does pain on the bottom of my foot mean?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Pain on the bottom of your foot most commonly indicates plantar fasciitis (especially if worst with first morning steps), metatarsalgia (ball of foot pain), or a stone bruise. Heel pain is the most reported foot complaint, affecting about 2 million Americans annually."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "When should I see a doctor for foot pain?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "See a doctor if you have severe swelling or bruising, cannot bear weight, pain persists beyond 2 weeks of home treatment, you notice numbness or tingling, there is an open wound or signs of infection, or the foot appears deformed. Sudden severe pain after an injury should be evaluated promptly."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why does my foot hurt in the morning when I first get up?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Morning foot pain that eases after walking is the hallmark symptom of plantar fasciitis. The plantar fascia tightens overnight, and the first steps stretch it painfully. Achilles tendonitis can also cause morning heel stiffness. Stretching before getting out of bed and wearing supportive footwear can help."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can foot pain be a sign of something serious?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "While most foot pain is caused by overuse or poorly fitting shoes, it can occasionally signal serious conditions like stress fractures, gout, peripheral neuropathy (nerve damage, often from diabetes), rheumatoid arthritis, or blood clots. Persistent, unexplained foot pain warrants medical evaluation."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the fastest way to relieve foot pain at home?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The RICE method (Rest, Ice, Compression, Elevation) is the first-line home treatment. Ice for 15-20 minutes several times daily, take over-the-counter anti-inflammatories like ibuprofen, roll your foot over a frozen water bottle, wear supportive shoes, and avoid the activity that triggered the pain. Most minor foot pain improves within 1-2 weeks."
      }
    }
  ]
};

export const meta = {
  title: "Foot Pain Chart: Interactive Diagram & Condition Finder",
  description: "Use our interactive foot pain chart to identify what's causing your foot pain. Click pain locations on the foot diagram to see likely conditions, symptoms, and treatments.",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-29"
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="bodycount"
  title="Foot Pain Chart: Interactive Diagram & Condition Finder"
  description="Use our interactive foot pain chart to identify what's causing your foot pain. Click pain locations on the foot diagram to see likely conditions, symptoms, and treatments."
  canonical="https://bodycount.photonbuilder.com/foot-pain-chart"
  schema={schema}
>
  <h1>Foot Pain Chart: Interactive Diagram & Condition Finder</h1>

  <style is:inline>
    :root {
      --bg-color: #060c0a;
      --card-bg: #0c1410;
      --border-color: #1a2a24;
      --accent-color: #2DB89A;
      --accent-hover: #24987f;
      --text-primary: #c8e0d8;
      --text-secondary: #888888;
      --font-ui: 'Inter', sans-serif;
      --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      --zone-common: #2DB89A;
      --zone-moderate: #f59e0b;
      --zone-serious: #ef4444;
      --zone-hover: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.3);
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    body {
      font-family: var(--font-ui);
      background-color: var(--bg-color);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      line-height: 1.6;
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }

    header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }

    h1 {
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    h3 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 1rem 0 0.5rem;
      color: var(--accent-color);
    }

    p, li { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem; }

    .intro-text {
      text-align: center;
      max-width: 650px;
      margin: 0 auto 2rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    /* Foot Map Section */
    .foot-map-section {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .foot-view {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .foot-view h3 {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .foot-svg-wrap {
      position: relative;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 280px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .foot-svg-wrap svg {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      display: block;
    }

    .foot-zone {
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: fill 0.2s, opacity 0.2s;
      opacity: 0.55;
    }

    .foot-zone:hover, .foot-zone.active {
      opacity: 0.85;
    }

    .legend {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin: 1rem 0;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .legend-item {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    .legend-dot {
      width: 12px;
      height: 12px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    /* Detail Panel */
    .detail-panel {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      display: none;
    }

    .detail-panel.visible { display: block; }

    .detail-panel h3 {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .detail-close {
      margin-left: auto;
      background: none;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      cursor: pointer;
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
    }

    .detail-close:hover { border-color: var(--accent-color); color: var(--text-primary); }

    .condition-card {
      background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.05);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .condition-card h4 {
      color: var(--accent-color);
      font-size: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .condition-rank {
      display: inline-block;
      background: var(--accent-color);
      color: #000;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      margin-right: 0.4rem;
      vertical-align: middle;
    }

    .condition-meta {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      margin-top: 0.75rem;
    }

    .condition-meta dt {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    }

    .condition-meta dd {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .red-flag {
      background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1);
      border: 1px solid rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.3);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
      margin-top: 0.75rem;
    }

    .red-flag strong { color: #ef4444; }
    .red-flag p { font-size: 0.85rem; }

    /* Symptom Checker */
    .quiz-section {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .quiz-step { display: none; }
    .quiz-step.active { display: block; }

    .quiz-question {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .quiz-progress {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    }

    .quiz-progress-dot {
      height: 4px;
      flex: 1;
      background: var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 2px;
      transition: background 0.3s;
    }

    .quiz-progress-dot.filled { background: var(--accent-color); }

    .quiz-options {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .quiz-option {
      background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.05);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      text-align: left;
      transition: border-color 0.2s, background 0.2s;
      font-family: var(--font-ui);
    }

    .quiz-option:hover {
      border-color: var(--accent-color);
      background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.1);
    }

    .quiz-option.selected {
      border-color: var(--accent-color);
      background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.15);
    }

    .quiz-nav {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .quiz-btn {
      background: var(--accent-color);
      color: #000;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 0.6rem 1.5rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-family: var(--font-ui);
      transition: background 0.2s;
    }

    .quiz-btn:hover { background: var(--accent-hover); }
    .quiz-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.4; cursor: not-allowed; }
    .quiz-btn.secondary {
      background: transparent;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      color: var(--text-primary);
    }
    .quiz-btn.secondary:hover { border-color: var(--accent-color); }

    .quiz-results {
      display: none;
    }

    .quiz-results.visible { display: block; }

    .result-card {
      background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.05);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .result-card h4 { color: var(--accent-color); margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }

    .result-likelihood {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.03em;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .likelihood-high { color: #2DB89A; }
    .likelihood-moderate { color: #f59e0b; }
    .likelihood-possible { color: #888; }

    /* Conditions Table */
    .table-wrap {
      overflow-x: auto;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 12px;
    }

    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
    }

    th {
      background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.08);
      text-align: left;
      padding: 0.75rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      cursor: pointer;
      white-space: nowrap;
      user-select: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    }

    th:hover { color: var(--accent-color); }
    th .sort-arrow { font-size: 0.7rem; margin-left: 0.3rem; }

    td {
      padding: 0.65rem 0.75rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    tr:hover td { background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.03); }

    .pain-dots {
      color: var(--zone-serious);
      letter-spacing: 2px;
    }

    .tag-yes {
      background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.15);
      color: #ef4444;
      padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
    }

    .tag-maybe {
      background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.15);
      color: #f59e0b;
      padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
    }

    .tag-no {
      background: rgba(45, 184, 154, 0.1);
      color: var(--accent-color);
      padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
    }

    /* Disclaimer */
    .disclaimer {
      background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.06);
      border: 1px solid rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1.25rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .disclaimer h3 { color: #ef4444; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .disclaimer p { font-size: 0.85rem; }

    /* FAQ */
    .faq-item {
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 8px;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .faq-q {
      padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      background: var(--card-bg);
    }

    .faq-q:hover { color: var(--accent-color); }

    .faq-arrow {
      transition: transform 0.2s;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    .faq-item.open .faq-arrow { transform: rotate(180deg); }

    .faq-a {
      max-height: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
    }

    .faq-item.open .faq-a { max-height: 300px; }

    .faq-a-inner {
      padding: 0 1rem 1rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .foot-map-section { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .quiz-options { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .condition-meta { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      h1 { font-size: 1.4rem; }
      h2 { font-size: 1.2rem; }
    }
  </style>

  <div class="container">
    <header>
      <p class="intro-text">Click any area on the foot diagram below to see likely conditions, symptoms, and treatment options. Use the symptom checker quiz for a personalized assessment.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="disclaimer">
      <h3>Medical Disclaimer</h3>
      <p>This tool is for <strong>educational purposes only</strong> and does not constitute medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. Always consult a qualified healthcare provider for any medical concerns. If you are experiencing severe pain, inability to bear weight, or signs of infection, seek immediate medical attention.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Interactive Foot Pain Map</h2>

    <div class="legend">
      <div class="legend-item"><div class="legend-dot" style="background:#2DB89A"></div> Common / Mild</div>
      <div class="legend-item"><div class="legend-dot" style="background:#f59e0b"></div> Moderate</div>
      <div class="legend-item"><div class="legend-dot" style="background:#ef4444"></div> Serious / Urgent</div>
    </div>

    <div class="foot-map-section">
      <!-- Top View -->
      <div class="foot-view">
        <h3>Top View (Right Foot)</h3>
        <div class="foot-svg-wrap">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 300 500" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" id="foot-top">
            <!-- Foot outline -->
            <path d="M150,480 C100,480 60,460 50,420 C40,380 42,340 45,300 C48,260 44,220 50,180 C56,140 70,110 90,90 C100,80 108,60 115,45 C120,35 128,25 140,22 C148,20 155,25 158,35 C160,42 165,55 172,58 C178,55 182,42 185,35 C188,28 192,22 198,22 C205,24 210,32 212,42 C216,55 218,50 222,48 C228,45 234,48 236,55 C240,68 238,60 242,58 C248,55 254,58 255,68 C258,80 254,72 256,75 C260,78 264,82 262,95 C258,110 248,100 242,98 C235,95 228,100 222,110 C210,140 205,170 200,200 C195,240 198,280 200,320 C202,360 210,400 200,440 C190,470 170,480 150,480 Z" fill="none" stroke="#1a2a24" stroke-width="2"/>

            <!-- Clickable zones — Top View -->
            <!-- Big toe -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="big-toe" cx="138" cy="42" rx="22" ry="28" fill="#2DB89A"/>
            <!-- Second toe -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="toes" cx="170" cy="50" rx="12" ry="20" fill="#2DB89A"/>
            <!-- Third toe -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="toes" cx="195" cy="46" rx="11" ry="18" fill="#2DB89A"/>
            <!-- Fourth toe -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="toes" cx="218" cy="52" rx="11" ry="17" fill="#2DB89A"/>
            <!-- Fifth toe -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="toes" cx="240" cy="65" rx="11" ry="17" fill="#2DB89A"/>

            <!-- Ball of foot -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="ball" cx="170" cy="115" rx="60" ry="30" fill="#f59e0b"/>

            <!-- Top of foot -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="top-of-foot" cx="150" cy="200" rx="50" ry="55" fill="#f59e0b"/>

            <!-- Arch area (visible from top as inner side) -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="arch" cx="95" cy="290" rx="25" ry="60" fill="#2DB89A"/>

            <!-- Outer edge -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="outer-edge" cx="205" cy="280" rx="20" ry="55" fill="#ef4444"/>

            <!-- Heel -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="heel" cx="140" cy="430" rx="45" ry="40" fill="#2DB89A"/>

            <!-- Ankle area (inner bump) -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="ankle" cx="80" cy="390" rx="22" ry="28" fill="#f59e0b"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Side View -->
      <div class="foot-view">
        <h3>Side View (Inner)</h3>
        <div class="foot-svg-wrap">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" id="foot-side">
            <!-- Foot outline side view -->
            <path d="M50,230 C50,210 55,190 80,170 C100,155 140,145 170,140 C200,135 240,120 270,100 C290,88 310,70 325,55 C332,48 340,42 348,45 C355,48 358,58 355,70 C350,90 340,100 330,105 C340,105 350,102 358,100 C365,98 370,102 368,110 C365,118 355,122 345,122 C352,123 360,120 365,118 C372,116 376,122 372,130 C368,138 355,140 345,138 C338,137 332,140 325,145 C310,155 280,165 250,175 C220,185 170,192 130,200 C100,206 70,215 55,225 C52,227 50,232 50,230 Z M50,230 L370,230" fill="none" stroke="#1a2a24" stroke-width="2"/>

            <!-- Ground line -->
            <line x1="30" y1="230" x2="390" y2="230" stroke="#1a2a24" stroke-width="1"/>

            <!-- Clickable zones — Side View -->
            <!-- Toes -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="toes" cx="348" cy="62" rx="14" ry="18" fill="#2DB89A"/>
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="big-toe" cx="355" cy="100" rx="16" ry="22" fill="#2DB89A"/>

            <!-- Ball of foot -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="ball" cx="310" cy="175" rx="30" ry="22" fill="#f59e0b"/>

            <!-- Top of foot -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="top-of-foot" cx="240" cy="130" rx="40" ry="22" fill="#f59e0b"/>

            <!-- Arch -->
            <path class="foot-zone" data-zone="arch" d="M160,225 Q200,185 280,220 L280,228 Q200,210 160,228 Z" fill="#2DB89A"/>

            <!-- Heel -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="heel" cx="80" cy="200" rx="35" ry="28" fill="#2DB89A"/>

            <!-- Ankle -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="ankle" cx="110" cy="140" rx="28" ry="24" fill="#f59e0b"/>

            <!-- Achilles area -->
            <ellipse class="foot-zone" data-zone="achilles" cx="70" cy="160" rx="16" ry="30" fill="#ef4444"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Detail Panel -->
    <div class="detail-panel" id="detail-panel">
      <h3 id="detail-title"><span id="detail-icon"></span> <span id="detail-name"></span> <button class="detail-close" id="detail-close">Close</button></h3>
      <div id="detail-content"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Symptom Checker Quiz -->
    <h2>Symptom Checker: What's Causing Your Foot Pain?</h2>
    <div class="quiz-section" id="quiz-section">
      <div class="quiz-progress" id="quiz-progress"></div>

      <div id="quiz-steps"></div>

      <div class="quiz-results" id="quiz-results">
        <h3>Your Results</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:0.85rem;">Based on your answers, these conditions are most likely. This is <strong>not a diagnosis</strong>.</p>
        <div id="quiz-results-list"></div>
        <button class="quiz-btn secondary" id="quiz-restart" style="margin-top:1rem;">Start Over</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Conditions Reference Table -->
    <h2>Foot Conditions Reference</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table id="conditions-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th data-col="name">Condition <span class="sort-arrow">▼</span></th>
            <th data-col="location">Location <span class="sort-arrow">▼</span></th>
            <th data-col="pain">Pain Level <span class="sort-arrow">▼</span></th>
            <th data-col="recovery">Recovery <span class="sort-arrow">▼</span></th>
            <th data-col="doctor">See Doctor? <span class="sort-arrow">▼</span></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody id="conditions-tbody"></tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-list" id="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What does pain on the bottom of my foot mean? <span class="faq-arrow">▾</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Pain on the bottom of your foot most commonly indicates plantar fasciitis (especially if worst with first morning steps), metatarsalgia (ball of foot pain), or a stone bruise. Heel pain is the most reported foot complaint, affecting about 2 million Americans annually. The location and timing of pain are key clues — arch pain that's worse in the morning suggests plantar fasciitis, while pain under the ball of the foot during push-off suggests metatarsalgia.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">When should I see a doctor for foot pain? <span class="faq-arrow">▾</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">See a doctor if you have severe swelling or bruising, cannot bear weight, pain persists beyond 2 weeks of home treatment, you notice numbness or tingling, there is an open wound or signs of infection (redness, warmth, fever), or the foot appears deformed. Sudden severe pain after an injury — especially with a popping sound — should be evaluated promptly to rule out fracture or tendon rupture.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Why does my foot hurt in the morning when I first get up? <span class="faq-arrow">▾</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Morning foot pain that eases after walking is the hallmark symptom of plantar fasciitis. The plantar fascia tightens overnight, and the first steps stretch it painfully. Achilles tendonitis can also cause morning heel stiffness. Stretching your calves and rolling your foot over a ball before getting out of bed, and wearing supportive footwear (even indoors), can significantly reduce morning pain.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can foot pain be a sign of something serious? <span class="faq-arrow">▾</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">While most foot pain is caused by overuse or poorly fitting shoes, it can occasionally signal serious conditions like stress fractures, gout (sudden severe big toe pain), peripheral neuropathy (nerve damage, often from diabetes), rheumatoid arthritis, or blood clots. Persistent, unexplained foot pain — especially accompanied by systemic symptoms like fever, fatigue, or unintended weight loss — warrants medical evaluation.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is the fastest way to relieve foot pain at home? <span class="faq-arrow">▾</span></div>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">The RICE method (Rest, Ice, Compression, Elevation) is the first-line home treatment. Ice for 15–20 minutes several times daily, take over-the-counter anti-inflammatories like ibuprofen, roll your foot over a frozen water bottle for combined massage and icing, wear supportive shoes, and avoid the activity that triggered the pain. Most minor foot pain improves within 1–2 weeks with consistent home care.</div></div>
      </div>
